Jacqueline Scott https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jacqueline_Scott 0 Jacqueline Sue Scott (born January 1, 1932) is an American actress who has appeared in several films and guest starred in more than 100 television programs. A TV Guide article once referred to her as "The Youngest Old-Timer in the Business" because she played opposite most of the leading men of the 1960s, 1970s, and 1980s.
